# Recommendation Memo

## Executive Summary

This analysis evaluated whether the Treatment experience should replace the existing Control experience using experiment results, hypothesis testing, KPI performance, and guardrail validation.

The decision framework did not rely only on conversion improvement. Supporting operational and customer-quality indicators were also reviewed before forming a recommendation.

Current recommendation:

**Continue Testing**

The treatment should not automatically move to full launch until statistical significance, revenue quality, and guardrail outcomes are confirmed.

---

# North Star Metric

## 30-Day Paid Revenue Growth

Definition:

Increase sustainable paid revenue generated within the first 30 days after acquisition.

This metric was selected because it captures both acquisition efficiency and monetization quality.

---

